quran[64]{c,v,t}:
  94,1,Have We not opened thy breast
  94,2,and eased thee of thy burden
  94,3,which galled thy back
  94,4,and raised thy reputation for thee
  94,5,Verily a difficulty shall be attended with ease
  94,6,Verily a difficulty shall be attended with ease
  94,7,"When thou shalt have ended thy preaching, labour to serve God in return for his favours"
  94,8,and make thy supplication unto thy Lord
  95,1,"By the fig, and the olive"
  95,2,and by mount Sinai
  95,3,and this territory of security
  95,4,Verily We created man of a most excellent fabric
  95,5,afterwards We rendered him the vilest of the vile
  95,6,"Except those who believe, and work righteousness; for they shall receive an endless reward"
  95,7,What therefore shall cause thee to deny the day of judgment after this
  95,8,Is not God the most wise judge
  96,1,"Read, in the name of thy Lord, Who hath created all things"
  96,2,who hath created man of congealed blood
  96,3,"Read, by thy most beneficent Lord"
  96,4,Who taught the use of the pen
  96,5,Who teacheth man that which he knoweth not
  96,6,Assuredly. Verily man becometh insolent
  96,7,because he seeth himself abound in riches
  96,8,Verily unto thy Lord shall be the return of all
  96,9,What thinkest thou as to him
  96,10,"who forbiddeth our servant, when he prayeth"
  96,11,What thinkest thou; if he follow the right direction
  96,12,or command piety
  96,13,"What thinkest thou; if he accuse the divine revelations of falsehood, and turn his back"
  96,14,Doth he not know that God seeth
  96,15,"Assuredly. Verily, if he forbear not, We will drag him by the forelock"
  96,16,"the lying, sinful forelock"
  96,17,And let him call his council to his assistance
  96,18,We also will call the infernal guards to cast him into hell
  96,19,"Assuredly. Obey him not: But continue to adore God; and draw nigh unto Him"
  97,1,Verily We sent down the Koran in the night of al Kadr
  97,2,And what shall make thee understand how excellent the night of al Kadr is
  97,3,The night of al Kadr is better than a thousand months
  97,4,"Therein do the angels descend, and the spirit Gabriel also, by the permission of their Lord, with his decrees concerning every matter"
  97,5,"It is peace, until the rising of the morn"
  98,1,"The unbelievers among those to whom the scriptures were given, and among the idolaters, did not stagger, until the clear evidence had come unto them"
  98,2,"An apostle from God, rehearsing unto them pure books of revelations"
  98,3,wherein are contained right discourses
  98,4,"Neither were they unto whom the scriptures were given divided among themselves, until after the clear evidence had come unto them"
  98,5,"And they were commanded no other in the scriptures than to worship God, exhibiting unto him the pure religion, and being orthodox; and to be constant at prayer, and to give alms: And this is the right religion"
  98,6,"Verily those who believe not, among those who have received the scriptures, and among the idolaters, shall be cast into the fire of hell, to remain therein for ever. These are the worst of creatures"
  98,7,"But they who believe, and do good works; these are the best of creatures"
  98,8,"Their reward with their Lord shall be gardens of perpetual abode, through which rivers flow; they shall remain therein for ever. God will be well pleased in them; and they shall be well pleased in him. This is prepared for him who shall fear his Lord"
  99,1,When the earth shall be shaken by an earthquake
  99,2,and the earth shall cast forth her burdens
  99,3,"and a man shall say, what aileth her"
  99,4,On that day the earth shall declare her tidings
  99,5,for that thy Lord will inspire her
  99,6,"On that day men shall go forward in distinct classes, that they may behold their works"
  99,7,"And whoever shall have wrought good of the weight of an ant, shall behold the same"
  99,8,"And whoever shall have wrought evil of the weight of an ant, shall behold the same"
  100,1,"By the war-horses which run swiftly to the battle, with a panting noise"
  100,2,"and by those which strike fire, by dashing their hoofs against the stones"
  100,3,and by those which make a sudden incursion on the enemy early in the morning
  100,4,and therein raise the dust
  100,5,and therein pass through the midst of the adverse troops
  100,6,Verily man is ungrateful unto his Lord
  100,7,and he is witness thereof
  100,8,And he is immoderate in the love of worldly good